---
/**
 * rest-api/0002 · Figure 1 — "three orthogonal properties: SAFE ⊂ IDEMPOTENT,
 * CACHEABLE is a separate axis".
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from docs/rest-api/lessons/0002-http-methods-and-status-codes.html
 * (figure + svg + figcaption). It lives as an .astro component, NOT inline in the
 * MDX, because MDX's JSX parser is unreliable with raw inline SVG that uses
 * kebab-case attributes (text-anchor, font-size, stroke-width, …). This figure
 * uses no arrowhead markers, so nothing extra is embedded.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 560 200"
        role="img"
        aria-label="Nested sets: safe methods are a subset of idempotent methods; cacheable overlaps safe; POST and PATCH sit outside idempotent"
    >
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <text
                x="280"
                y="18"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="12"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#111110">SAFE ⊂ IDEMPOTENT · CACHEABLE IS A SEPARATE AXIS</text
            >
            <rect
                x="40"
                y="34"
                width="340"
                height="148"
                rx="12"
                fill="#fff"
                stroke="#1f3a5a"
                stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
            <text
                x="210"
                y="52"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10.5"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#1f3a5a">IDEMPOTENT — repeat = same state</text
            >
            <rect
                x="60"
                y="64"
                width="180"
                height="104"
                rx="10"
                fill="#eef5ee"
                stroke="#2f5d3a"
                stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
            <text
                x="150"
                y="82"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#2f5d3a">SAFE — read-only intent</text
            >
            <text
                x="150"
                y="104"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="13"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#2f5d3a">GET · HEAD</text
            >
            <text
                x="150"
                y="124"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="13"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#2f5d3a">OPTIONS</text
            >
            <text x="150" y="150" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#244a2e"
                >cacheable by default →</text
            >
            <text
                x="310"
                y="104"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="13"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#1f3a5a">PUT</text
            >
            <text
                x="310"
                y="126"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="13"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#1f3a5a">DELETE</text
            >
            <text x="310" y="150" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
                >change state, but converge</text
            >
            <rect
                x="402"
                y="64"
                width="150"
                height="104"
                rx="10"
                fill="#f7ecea"
                stroke="#9a2417"
                stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
            <text
                x="477"
                y="84"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#9a2417">NOT IDEMPOTENT</text
            >
            <text
                x="477"
                y="108"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="13"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#9a2417">POST</text
            >
            <text
                x="477"
                y="132"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="13"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#9a2417">PATCH*</text
            >
            <text x="477" y="156" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#7a2218"
                >*depends on the patch doc</text
            >
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        "Safe" ≠ "secure": a <code>GET</code> may log or run analytics — it just isn't
        <em>intended</em> to change resource state. Cacheability is independent of the other two axes.
    </figcaption>
</figure>
